    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="629"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d629">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">417.41/13</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 519</seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The British Embassy present their compliments to the Department of State and have
                    the honour to refer to the Department’s memorandum of April 30th,<note n="10"
                        xml:id="d629fn10">Not printed.</note> in which it was stated that the Public
                        <pb facs="0752" n="667" xml:id="pg_667"/> Credit Commission in Nicaragua had
                    agreed to increase its offer for the settlement of the British claims to a total
                    of £9000.0.0. cash and £2000.0.0. bonds.</p>
                <p>This offer was communicated by telegram to the British Government, from whom a
                    reply has now been received expressing their regret that they are unable to
                    accept the offer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 14, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
